narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: The course was absolutely incredibly--I learned not just about the complexities of literature, in form and style, but also in content. Kundera cut across disciplines: history, philosophy, art. One of the best courses I've taken at Yale.
We got the opportunity to explore the works of one of the greatest contemporary writers of our time, Milan Kundera.

comments: Definitely. Professor von Kunes is incredibly, and the only way to read Kundera is to read his entire chronology.
Take it! It's so much fun and Prof. Kunes is a joy!
